Your creative potential has no limits.

Are you tired of playing it safe? Do you crave a breakthrough in your creative journey? 

Then listen closely, because it’s time to embrace the power of taking creative risks!

In a world full of imitation and conformity, it’s those who dare to step out of their comfort zones that leave a lasting impact. 

Taking creative risks isn’t just about standing out; it’s about discovering the extraordinary within you.

Look at history’s trailblazers. They didn’t settle for mediocrity; they disrupted entire industries by challenging the status quo.

When you take creative risks, you expand your horizons. Your mind opens up to new possibilities and unique perspectives. 

It’s through these risks that breakthrough ideas emerge, propelling you towards success.

Don’t be afraid to fail. Failure is merely a stepping stone towards growth and innovation. 

Remember, every great success story is built upon a series of courageous leaps of faith.

So, unleash your imagination, break free from the ordinary, and take that leap into the unknown. 

Dare to be different, and watch your creativity soar!

Feeling a little more confident about taking that creative leap?

Share this with someone else who could use this helpful reminder. 👍

#creativity #entrepreneur #entrepreneurship #inspiration #creativeart

Last weekend, @smokedspicebbq & @hungryartistny hosted their BBQ pop-up at @finbackbrewery 🔥 A diverse crowd of OVER 200 people pulled up to support and all items SOLD OUT in less than 3 hours! The event aimed to bring our community together through great food and vibes. Smoke Spice BBQ’s menu included various Caribbean Texas style fusion items such as Brisket Sandwiches on homemade Coco Bread, Smoked BBQ Oxtail, Jerk Fried Rice, Honey Cornbread Pudding, and more.

🎬 Big THANKS to the talented @brandonbassador of @superwellstudios, who filmed and edited this video to recap the pop-up. His recap cinematically highlights the amazing food, energy, and people that took part in the event and shows some candid reactions from those that attended. Make sure to check out his work!

PART 1/5 👉 This week, I’m running through my current 📸 gear bag and sharing my 5 most important tools.

First up (obviously) is the camera kit. Here’s what I’m shooting with:

Camera Kit: Nikon Z5
Primary Lens: NIKKOR 50mm Prime Lens

This quality content creation combo is ideal for any aspiring photographers or videographers to jumpstart their careers. Just make sure you’re shootout in Manual Mode 😉 (more on why on the way soon).

📲 Follow along to discover what else I’m carrying around on shoot days. I’m posting one new featured item every day through Friday. 

#nikon #nikonphotography #photography #photographylovers #photographylover #photographyislife #photogram #cameratips #camerasetup #cameragear

PART 2/5 👉 This week, I’m running through my current 📸 gear bag and sharing my 5 most important tools.

Next up is the gimbal. Here’s why it’s important for any videographer 🎬:

1️⃣ Stabilizes any shaky camera movement for smoother footage. 🫨 

2️⃣ Looks really cool when you use it on set. 😎 

Gimbal: @djiglobal Ronin SC

It might seem intimidating at first but once you figure out how to balance the gimbal, your videos will be taken to unexpected levels of awesomeness! 🔥 

📲 Follow along to discover what else I’m carrying around on shoot days. I’m posting one new featured item every day through Friday. 

#nikon #nikonphotography #photography #photographylovers #photographylover #photographyislife #photogram #cameratips #camerasetup #cameragear #dji #djironin #gimbal #gimbaloperator #gimbalstabilizer

PART 3/5 👉 This week, I’m running through my current 📸 gear bag and sharing my 5 most important tools.

Next up is the microphone 🎤 Here’s why it’s important for any videographer 🎬:

1️⃣ Allows for clean, clear voiceover content without the wind or excess noise.

2️⃣ Looks really cool when you use it on set. 😎 

Mic: @rodemic Wireless GO II ✌️ 

There are multiple ways to get clean audio for your video footage but having a reliable, professional wireless mic setup is key for mastering audio.🔥

Morning's Citrus Symphony 🍊☀️🚊

🎬 Introducing a new series in collaboration with @superwellstudios. A collection of originally, prompted AI-generated poetry designed to inspire you to take action in your life.

~
Beneath night's veil, a quiet disguise,
The sunrise brings forth a citrusy prize.

Like an orange ripe with vibrant delight,
It gently chases away the night.

The stars, they twinkle, bid goodbye,
As the sun ascends the morning sky.

With a warm smile and a zesty kiss,
It whispers, "New day, embrace the bliss."

So rise, my friend, with zest in your heart,
Let the sunrise give your day a start.

In its citrusy glow, find your way,
For each dawn brings a brand-new day.
~

🎬 Ep 1 | In the Portland, OR area and thinking about going vegan? Meet Kimberley and Dee of @gibbongrub 🌭🪴🍔

Co-founders of this epic, underrated food stand, there’s a real love and passion for everything they make on their incredibly organized and cozy truck on the side of SE Lexington St. 🚚💨

And yes, I ate both the Bomb Burger and Chicago Dog. Both were 12/10 🏆😋 

🚨 They’re open almost every day but Thursday! Say hi the next time you’re in town. 👋 

#SuperQuickStories #SuperWell

🎬 Ep 2 | Have a dog in need of walking in the UES of Manhattan? 🐩 Meet Raymond Torres of @innerwolfnyc. 

This amazing New Yorker is kind, smart, and incredibly creative. Reviews from his clients are 10/10 and they couldn’t imagine having a dog in the city without Raymond’s care and expertise. 🏆 

And the best part? He captures pics of the dogs during their daily walks so their owners can see how happy they are! 📸🐶
